<collectingCountry box="[515,604,341,366]" name="Sweden" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sweden</collectingCountry>
.—Transpalearctic: from West Europe to 
<collectingCountry box="[1065,1174,341,366]" name="Mongolia" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[1188,1397,341,366]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 232" refId="ref58506" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1959) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Brucksichtigung der europaischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32, 1 - 232." type="journal article" year="1959">Linsenmaier 1959</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,341,510]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,377,402]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species has been found from 
<collectingCountry box="[689,795,377,402]" name="Denmark" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Denmark</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[806,877,377,402]" name="Latvia" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Latvia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[929,1020,377,402]" name="Sweden" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sweden</collectingCountry>
. It is very rare and has been classified as critically endangered in 
<collectingCountry box="[446,534,413,438]" name="Sweden" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sweden</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cederberg, B. &amp; Abenius, J. &amp; Hellqvist, S. &amp; Hogmo, O. &amp; Larsson, M. &amp; Sorensson, M." box="[548,792,413,438]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="345 - 360" refId="ref53093" refString="Cederberg, B., Abenius, J., Hellqvist, S., Hogmo, O., Larsson, M. &amp; Sorensson, M. (2010) Steklar - Wasps, Hymenoptera. In: Gardenfors, U. (Ed.), Rodlistade arter i Sverige 2010 - The 2010 Red List of Swedish Species. ArtDatabanken, SLU, Uppsala, pp. 345 - 360." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Cederberg 
<emphasis box="[671,726,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Recently it was recorded in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1219,1307,413,438]" name="Sweden" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sweden</collectingCountry>
for the first time in 50 years. 
<bibRefCitation author="Balthasar, V." box="[344,530,449,474]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 272" refId="ref51745" refString="Balthasar, V. (1954) Zlatenky - Chrysidoidea (Rad: Blanokridli - Hymenoptera). Fauna CSR, 3, 1 - 272." type="journal article" year="1954">Balthasar (1954)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar, L." box="[584,750,449,474]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref59142" refString="Moczar, L. (1967) Femdarazsalkatuak - Chrysidoidea. Fauna Hungariae, 86, 1 - 118. [Budapest]" type="journal article" year="1967">Móczár (1967)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1046,1134,449,474]" name="Finland" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Finland</collectingCountry>
, but these records are most likely erroneous, as 
<bibRefCitation author="Vikberg, V." box="[373,555,485,510]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="61 - 64" refId="ref64006" refString="Vikberg, V. (1986 a) Notes on some taxa of Hymenoptera Apocrita Aculeata. Notulae Entomologicae, 66, 61 - 64." type="journal article" year="1986">Vikberg (1986a)</bibRefCitation>
noted. No Finnish specimens have been found from collections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
